We have that $r = \sqrt{(-2)^2 + (-2)^2} = 2 \sqrt{2}.$  Also, if we draw the line connecting the origin and $(-2,2),$ this line makes an angle of $\frac{5 \pi}{4}$ with the positive $x$-axis.

