Then $\angle A$ is maximized when $\overline{AC}$ is tangent to the circle.  In this case, $\angle C = 90^\circ,$ so by Pythagoras,
\[AC = \sqrt{20^2 - 15^2} = 5 \sqrt{7}.\]Then $\tan A = \frac{15}{5 \sqrt{7}} = \boxed{\frac{3 \sqrt{7}}{7}}.$

