Because $\triangle ATE$ and $\triangle ADF$ are similar, we have \[
\frac{DF}{x} = \frac{AD}{AT} = \frac{4}{3},\]and \[DF=\frac{4x}{3}.
\]Also, $\triangle BEC$ and $\triangle DFC$ are similar, so \[
