draw((1,-0.3)--(1,1.3),red);
draw((-0.3,0)--(1.3,0));
draw((0,-0.3)--(0,1.3));
[/asy]

Hence, the region we are interested in is simply the square with vertices $(0,0),$ $(1,0),$ $(1,1),$ and $(0,1),$ which has area $\boxed{1}.$

Because triangle $ABC$ is similar to triangle $XYZ,$ $\frac{AB}{XY}=\frac{BC}{YZ}.$ Plugging in the values we are given yields \begin{align*}
\frac{4}{14} &= \frac{6}{YZ}\\
